revision.text:
{{other uses|Erica (disambiguation)}}
'''ERICA''', or the '''Experiment on Rapidly Intensifying Cyclones over the Atlantic''', is a scientific field project that started in the winter of 1988/1989.<ref name="FcstOceanicCyc">{{cite web | title = Forecasting Oceanic Cyclones At The NOAA |author1=Joseph M. Sienkiewicz |author2=Scott Prosise |author3=Anthony Crutch | publisher = [[Ocean Prediction Center]] (NOAA) | date = May 14, 2004 | url = http://www.opc.ncep.noaa.gov/SOO/papers/FORECASTING%20OCEANIC%20CYCLONES%20AT%20THE%20NOAA.pdf | accessdate = October 29, 2006 }}</ref> Its aims were to better understand the processes involved in rapid [[cyclogenesis]], and so improve understanding and [[forecasting]] of the situations that cause it.

==See also ==
*[[The Hurricane Rainband and Intensity Change Experiment|RAINEX]]

