{{Coord|36|N|105|E|region:CN_type:mountain|display=title}}
'''Lanshan''' mountain range (Ch. 兰山) is a  mountain range along northern shore of the [[Yellow River]] east from the capital [[Lanzhou]] of the [[Gansu]] [[Province of China|province]] in northwestern [[China]].

The area of the Lanshan mountains played a prominent role in the history of early China, 
changing hands many times in the course of events, after the fall of the [[Han Dynasty]]  there was located a capital of a succession of states, in the 4th century it was a capital of the independent state [[Earlier Liang]], and from the 5th to the 11th century it became a center for [[Buddhism|Buddhist]] study in China.

