{{Infobox oil field | name = Shebelinka | country = [[Ukraine]] | region = [[Kharkov Oblast]] | location = | block = | offonshore = onshore | coordinates = | operator = [[Ukrnafta]] | operators = | partners = | contractors = | image = | caption = | discovery = 1956 | start_development = 1956 | start_production = 1958 | abandonment = | peak_year = | peak_of_production_oil_bbl/d = | peak_of_production_oil_tpy = | peak_of_production_gas_mmcuft/d = | peak_of_production_gas_mmscm/d = | peak_of_production_gas_bcm/y = | oil_production_bbl/d = | oil_production_tpy = | production_year_oil = | production_gas_mmcuft/d = | production_gas_mmscm/d = | production_gas_bcm/y = | production_year_gas = | est_oil_bbl = | est_oil_t = | recover_oil_bbl = | recover_oil_t = | est_gas_bft = | est_gas_bcm = | recover_gas_bft =18400 | recover_gas_bcm =520 | formations = }}
The '''Shebelinka gas field''' is a [[Ukraine|Ukrainian]] [[natural gas field]] that was discovered in 1956. It began production in 1958 and produces [[natural gas]] and [[Natural gas condensate|condensates]]. The total [[proven reserves]] of the Shebelinka gas field are around 18.4 trillion cubic feet (520×10<sup>9</sup>m³).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fox-davies.com/media/1263/fdc_ukraine_report.pdf|title=Ukraine oil and gas report|date=December 2005|publisher=Fox Davies|accessdate=30 December 2010}}</ref>
